modules.description: This module implements HTTP clients for Twirp RPC services using the Ezcurl library, providing synchronous `call` and `call_exn` functions to invoke unary RPC methods over HTTP with support for JSON or binary encoding. It handles request headers as string pairs, error reporting with formatted printing, and optional TLS and client configuration. Concrete use cases include calling Twirp-based microservices from OCaml applications, with direct control over hosts, ports, and request metadata.
